The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Tuesday, November 02, 2004 

 SC arrears ire at officers

 New Delhi, Nov. 1: Bengal?s chief secretary and principal secretary (home) could face contempt of the Supreme Court, which today took serious note of their absence to answer charges regarding payment of arrears to the West Bengal Border Wing Home-Guards.

 A division bench of Justices Y.K. Sabharwal and D.M. Dharmadhikari ordered the state government to file a ?compliance? report in a week.

 The case relates to the payment of arrears worth Rs 38 crore to the force set up in 1977 to assist the BSF check infiltration from Bangladesh. 

 Bus loot: A CSTC bus to Malda was looted in Murshidabad this evening. The district police chief said dacoits armed with revolvers looted the passengers at Ratanpore More in Sagardighi on National Highway 34, 235 km from Calcutta.




